            <p>PUBLIC LEDGER<lb/>
                S. W. Corner Sixth and Chestnut Sts.<lb/></p>
            <p>GEORGE W. CHILDS&#44; PROPRIETOR.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; Aug. 26 1882<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#8212;Have<lb/> just returned to the<lb/> city after an absence<lb/> of nearly two weeks &#38;<lb/> have received your card<lb/> in relation to the publi&#45;<lb/>cation in the <hi rend="underline">Record</hi><lb/> etc.  Before leaving<lb/> the city I requested the<lb/> city editor to send you<lb/> the proofs of the sketch&#44;<lb/> but as the article was<lb/> to appear on the next<lb/> day&#44; it seems that<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>they had not time<lb/> to send them.  I should<lb/> have been glad for you<lb/> to have had them so<lb/> that the corrections &#38;<lb/> additions might have<lb/> been made.  I labored<lb/> under considerable dif&#45;<lb/>ficulty in gathering<lb/> the facts for the sketch<lb/> &#38; but for your kind<lb/> cooperation would not<lb/> have succeeded.  With<lb/> many thanks for your<lb/> aid &#38; services I am<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours respectfully<lb/>
                William Hilt<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
